title: Nore's Slumbo
summary: Nore's Slumbo might be a good recipe to expand your main course recipe box. Watching your figure? This gluten free and pescatarian recipe has 386 calories, 31g of protein, and 12g of fat per serving. This recipe serves 8 and costs $4.68 per serving. It is brought to you by Foodnetwork. 37 people have made this recipe and would make it again. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 1 hour and 35 minutes. Head to the store and pick up bay leaf, tomato paste, butter, and a few other things to make it today. instructions: Heat butter and oil in a 6 to 7-quart stock pot over medium-high heat. Add onions, celery, pepper, and garlic and saute for 5 minutes, until softened and slightly caramelized. Add gumbo powder, bay leaf, cayenne, paprika, salt, thyme, oregano and pepper and continue cooking, another minute. Add tomato paste and cook until it browns, another 4 minutes. Add seafood stock, bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Right before serving, add haddock and continue to simmer for 5 minutes, then add remaining seafood. Cook another 5 minutes. Add hot sauce, and season with salt and pepper, to taste. Serve over rice and sprinkle with file powder.

steps.step: Heat butter and oil in a 6 to 7-quart stock pot over medium-high heat.
Add onions, celery, pepper, and garlic and saute for 5 minutes, until softened and slightly caramelized.
Add gumbo powder, bay leaf, cayenne, paprika, salt, thyme, oregano and pepper and continue cooking, another minute.
Add tomato paste and cook until it browns, another 4 minutes.
Add seafood stock, bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Right before serving, add haddock and continue to simmer for 5 minutes, then add remaining seafood. Cook another 5 minutes.
Add hot sauce, and season with salt and pepper, to taste.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with file powder.
